new congress of peoples deputies in his capital kiev he is 
ukrainian an engineer and lifelong party bureaucrat 
viktor m chebrikov 66 the former kgb chief who last year was 
promoted to the politburo and given the job of running the criminal 
justice system a russian he worked as an engineer for two years 
before moving to party jobs in the ukraine he was deputy chairman 
and then chairman of the kgb from 1968 to 1988 during two decades of 
crackdowns on dissidents 
viktor p nikonov 60 a agricultural and party bureaucrat he is 
a russian who moved to moscow as deputy minister of agriculture in 
1979 in last years politburo shakeup he became yegor k 
ligachevs deputy in the party commission on agriculture 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
yuri f solovyov 65 the leningrad regional party chief who 
despite running unopposed lost election to a seat in the congress 
last spring when more than 50 percent of the voters crossed his name 
off the ballot reformers in the leningrad communist party 
successfully demanded his removal from the party leadership a 
russian he spent 22 years as a subway construction engineer in 
leningrad before moving to party work in 1974 
nikolai v talyzin 60 gorbachevs first choice for planning 
chief in 1985 who was demoted last year when the kremlin opted for 
more radical decentralization of the economy the russian engineer 
