all 13 of its annual appropriations bills before the august recess 
but only one has been forwarded to the presidents desk because 
action in the senate has been stalled over the drug controversy 
acknowledging the mess the house appropriations committee has 
tentatively scheduled a meeting next tuesday to approve a 31day 
interim spending bill which would prevent the government from 
shutting down oct 1 
