possible release of nelson mandela walter sisulu and other jailed 
leaders of the outlawed african national congress guerrilla 
movement mandela is serving a life sentence since his 1962 
conviction for sabotage 
the draft resisters include many who have yet to be drafted and 
others who have completed their twoyear training but say they will 
not attend mandatory callup camps 
we are not prepared to serve in a racist defense force to 
uphold a racist system said chris de villiers a lawyer and 
