in madrid to discuss renewing diplomatic and trade relations 
such a move would in effect set aside for now the dispute 
stemming from their rival claims of sovereignty over the falklands 
the islands off argentina have been ruled by britain since 1833 
argentina claims it inherited the territory which it calls the 
malvinas when it declared independence from spain in 1810 
argentina invaded the islands inhabited by about 1800 people of 
british descent on april 2 1982 britain counterattacked and 
defeated argentina in a war that helped contribute to the downfall 
of the military junta that ruled from 1976 until raul alfonsin was 
