<TEXT>
allergic reactions to foods may be responsible 
for dizziness hearing loss and ringing in the ears among thousands 
of people who suffer a disorder called menieres disease a study 
concludes 
the study of 49 patients with the innerear disorder was 
conducted by dr jennifer derebery of the house ear institute the 
institutes president is dr john house former president reagans 
ear doctor 
the 49 underwent testing to determine their food allergies then 
those foods were removed from their diets vertigo either was 
reduced or eliminated in 66 percent of the patients half 
experienced a decrease in ringing in their ears and several had 
dramatic improvements in hearing 
the foods most commonly linked to menieres disease were wheat 
eggs milk corn yeast and soybeans 
thousands of americans have the disease in which excess fluid 
accumulates in the labyrinth the part of the inner ear that 
controls balance 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
food engineering students cooked up 800 
pounds of popcorn in an effort to combat the toothjarring plague 
that afflicts popcorn lovers everywhere upks also known as 
unpopped kernels 
there are two basic problems that appear to cause an increase 
in upks and a decrease in popping volume shelling of the kernel off 
the cob and the moisture content of individual kernels at the time 
of popping said steven eckhoff a food engineer at the university 
of illinois at urbanachampaign 
during the summer food engineering students using a movie 
theater popper found that unpopped kernels were most likely those 
that were too moist or too dry large kernels at the butt of an ear 
of corn have the highest moisture content small kernels near the 
tip have the lowest 
it follows then that companies could process kernels of 
uniform size to decrease the number of unpopped kernels the 
university said 
the researchers also found that if a kernels outside covering is 
damaged when kernels are removed from the cob steam cant build up 
inside the kernel that also creates those dreaded upks 
were looking at ways to precondition the corn to loosen the 
attachment of the kernel to the cob so you wouldnt need as much 
mechanical force eckhoff said then you wouldnt damage the 
kernels so much 
the research was funded by beatricehuntwesson foods parent 
company of popcorn maker orville redenbacher 
