getting the problem into a different zone its going to allow for 
greater focus on its core earnings base 
with the big charge chases total reserve for possible credit 
losses at the end of the third quarter will be about 37 billion 
this includes about 29 billion for loans to developing nations 
or about 46 percent of chases total 62 billion of medium and 
longterm loans to third world countries the ratio had been 26 
percent 
the major new york money center banks generally have loan loss 
reserves equalling roughly a third of their outstanding third world 
loans chases new reserve ratio will lead the pack 
major banks have been under increasing pressure lately to boost 
their reserves to cover third world debt in the aftermath of the 
recent mexico debt agreement and the plan by treasury secretary 
nicholas brady that emphasizes bank forgiveness of these accounts 
this action resulted from our ongoing review of economic and 
political conditions and our belief that recent developments 
including the brady initiative have resulted in increased pressure 
on banks to reduce their claims and an increased resistance on 
the part of some lesser developed nations to meet their contractual 
obligations butcher said 
he said the pressure has become apparent in the nowcompleted 
mexican negotiations and the negotiating positions announced by 
other countries 
