for working capital included in the total buyout cost 
in addition to management personnel and united pilots the buyout 
group includes british airways plc as a minority partner 
the group plans to finance the transaction with 750 million from 
british airways 200 million in voluntary pension contributions 
from the pilots 13 billion from ual cash reserves and 72 
billion in bank loans 
the buyout would give ual nonmanagement employees 75 percent 
ownership 
