jp morgan amp co inc moved ahead of other major 
banking companies thursday by adding 2 billion to its cushion of 
reserves for loan losses indicating deeper pessimism about the 
chances of repayment by developing countries 
morgans action was far more severe than those taken earlier this 
week by chase manhattan corp and manufacturers hanover corp 
morgans reserves now equal 100 percent of its medium and 
longterm loans to developing countries in contrast chases equal 
46 percent after its addition this week and manufacturers hanovers 
36 percent 
