<TEXT>
the chairman of berkshire hathaway inc 
investor warren e buffett said wednesday he now has federal 
regulators permission to vote his stock in usair as provided by a 
previous agreement 
in a filing with the securities and exchange commission buffett 
said the waiting period for approval of the agreement under federal 
antitrust law expired sept 13 
buffett who bought 358 miilion in newly issued convertible 
preferred stock in usair group inc last month said the expiration 
of the waiting period gave him clearance from the federal trade 
commission to exercise his voting rights under the agreement 
buffetts shares described by him and usair as a friendly 
investment gave him a 12 percent stake in the company which runs 
the nations seventhlargest airline 
in july a new york investor group headed by wall street money 
manager michael steinhardt said it acquired 598 percent of usair 
and might seek control of the arlington vabased airline company 
the group said in a recent sec filing that it had increased its 
holding to 838 percent through stock purchases between sept 7 and 
monday 
